The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically the problem of guarding a polygon with few guards. This falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the use of different approaches and algorithms to solve the problem, which could fall under data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also mentions the NP-hardness of the problem, which could fall under complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of graphs to represent the polygon, which could fall under graph theory (cs.GT).
